Responsibilities : 
Specific Functional duties include: 
Design, Development and Implementation of Service Integration and Management processes 
Conduct client workshops, interviews and presentations 
Writing functional requirements for systems implementations and system test scripts 
Perform quality reviews to ensure requirements are documented properly 
ServiceNow customization including, but not limited to: core setup, workflow administration, reporting, data imports, LDAP integration, custom scripting, ebonding, and third party software integrations. 
Minimum 3 years Change and MIM experience 
Minimum of 3 years of Service Integration and Management experience 
Minimum of 3 years of experience from professional services organization 
Minimum of 2 years of experience with ServiceNow or BMC Remedy ITSM as super/advanced user 
Experience as Functional/ Business Process Consultant in deployments of ServiceNow applications 
Understanding of Service Blueprints, Service Definitions and Service Modeling 
Experience with user acceptance testing (UAT), including test script creation, execution and signoffs 
Requirements : 
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills 
Excellent verbal and written communication skills 
Strong presentation development and Customer Presentation skills 
Strong skills in data reporting, presentation and analysis 
Successful teamwork experience & demonstrated leadership abilities 
Strong familiarity with Service Desk Operations and Processes 
ITIL Certification 
